text.section:
The Mayor and Council of Ocean City may:
Employ and set the salaries for a Convention Hall manager and other necessary personnel;
Accept donations or grants for the maintenance and operation of the Convention Hall and receive any aid from the federal government, the State, or from local governments;
Set reasonable charges for the use and rental of the facilities of the Convention Hall;
Grant, upon the basis of competitive bidding, concessions on the premises of the Convention Hall to concessionaires for the sale of food or beverages, including alcoholic beverages subject to the provisions of Article 2B of this Code; and
Perform any acts necessary and proper for the administration and operation of the Convention Hall.
